[{"data":1,"prerenderedAt":683},["ShallowReactive",2],{"header-locale:\u002Fen\u002Fai\u002F2025\u002F05\u002F22\u002Fgithub-copilot-mcp-server-vscode-setup\u002F":3,"page:\u002Fen\u002Fai\u002F2025\u002F05\u002F22\u002Fgithub-copilot-mcp-server-vscode-setup\u002F":4,"alt:\u002Fen\u002Fai\u002F2025\u002F05\u002F22\u002Fgithub-copilot-mcp-server-vscode-setup\u002F":3,"prev-next:\u002Fen\u002Fai\u002F2025\u002F05\u002F22\u002Fgithub-copilot-mcp-server-vscode-setup\u002F":658,"related:\u002Fen\u002Fai\u002F2025\u002F05\u002F22\u002Fgithub-copilot-mcp-server-vscode-setup\u002F":667},"\u002Fai\u002F20250522\u002F3579637231\u002F",{"id":5,"title":6,"abbrlink":7,"altUrl":3,"body":8,"category":639,"date":640,"description":641,"extension":642,"lang":643,"meta":644,"navigation":645,"path":646,"readingMinutes":647,"seo":648,"standalone":649,"stem":650,"tags":651,"tldr":655,"updated":640,"url":656,"__hash__":657},"content\u002Fen\u002FAI\u002Fgithub-copilot-mcp-server-vscode-setup.md","GitHub Copilot + MCP Server in VSCode: Build Your AI Dev Workflow","4625108374",{"type":9,"value":10,"toc":631},"minimark",[11,19,24,27,31,34,37,40,43,46,49,52,86,89,93,96,112,115,121,134,139,142,147,150,192,195,198,204,211,449,456,460,463,472,475,486,492,495,498,503,512,516,523,534,537,543,546,552,555,561,565,568,574,577,580,586,589,601,604,607,613,616,621,624,627],[12,13,14],"p",{},[15,16],"img",{"alt":17,"src":18},"GitHub Copilot + MCP Server","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002Fblog\u002Fai\u002Fmcp-github-copilot\u002FChatGPT%20Image%202025%E5%B9%B45%E6%9C%8822%E6%97%A5%20%E4%B8%8A%E5%8D%8810_50_58.png",[20,21,23],"h2",{"id":22},"intro","Intro",[12,25,26],{},"These days, AI development has become a must-have skill for engineers, but when we use AI tools we keep running into the same issues — the AI returns something we didn't expect, or it just can't grasp what we want. These problems hit our productivity hard. So to solve this, MCP Server came along.",[20,28,30],{"id":29},"what-is-mcp-server","What is MCP Server?",[12,32,33],{},"In short, MCP (Model Context Protocol) is an AI protocol — the concept is the same as the HTTP protocol. As long as everyone follows the protocol, they can talk to \u002F connect with each other.",[12,35,36],{},"If we try to explain this in one big paragraph, it gets confusing fast, so let me put it more simply:",[12,38,39],{},"\"Everyone agrees on a set of game rules, then everyone follows those rules, so they can all play the game together.\"",[12,41,42],{},"Why put it that way? Every service provider has their own rules — GitHub, Figma, Google, etc. Each of these services has its own API, and each API plays by its own rules. There's no way the AI can know all of those rules, so we use a kind of consultant to handle this stuff for us. That middleman is the MCP Server.",[12,44,45],{},"Take GitHub as an example. When we send a request through GitHub Copilot, GitHub Copilot first analyzes and breaks down the request. When it figures out the request is GitHub-related, it goes to the MCP Server and says, \"hey, I have a GitHub-related request — could you check with GitHub about where these things are?\" The MCP Server flips through its manual (the API docs) and tells GitHub Copilot, \"this thing is over here\", then runs\u002Fresponds based on your request.",[12,47,48],{},"This approach significantly increases AI accuracy, and it lets the AI know what you're actually talking about — so you stop getting answers that don't match what you wanted.",[12,50,51],{},"OK, with that out of the way, let's get to the main topic. Before we start, you need to have these set up (and installed):",[53,54,55,65,72,79],"ul",{},[56,57,58],"li",{},[59,60,64],"a",{"href":61,"rel":62},"https:\u002F\u002Fcode.visualstudio.com\u002F",[63],"nofollow","Visual Studio Code",[56,66,67],{},[59,68,71],{"href":69,"rel":70},"https:\u002F\u002Fmarketplace.visualstudio.com\u002Fitems?itemName=GitHub.copilot",[63],"GitHub Copilot",[56,73,74],{},[59,75,78],{"href":76,"rel":77},"https:\u002F\u002Fmarketplace.visualstudio.com\u002Fitems?itemName=GitHub.copilot-chat",[63],"GitHub Copilot Chat",[56,80,81],{},[59,82,85],{"href":83,"rel":84},"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.docker.com\u002F",[63],"Docker",[12,87,88],{},"Once you've got these in place, we can keep going.",[20,90,92],{"id":91},"configuring-and-getting-an-mcp-server","Configuring and getting an MCP Server",[12,94,95],{},"So how do we find the MCP Server we want? There are two places to grab them:",[53,97,98,105],{},[56,99,100],{},[59,101,104],{"href":102,"rel":103},"https:\u002F\u002Fmodelcontextprotocol.io\u002Fexamples",[63],"Official MCP Examples page",[56,106,107],{},[59,108,111],{"href":109,"rel":110},"https:\u002F\u002Fgithub.com\u002Fmodelcontextprotocol\u002Fservers",[63],"MCP Servers repository",[12,113,114],{},"You can find MCP Servers worth trying in either place. For this demo I'll pick GitHub's MCP Server.",[12,116,117],{},[15,118],{"alt":119,"src":120},"GitHub MCP Server","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002Fblog\u002Fai\u002Fmcp-github-copilot\u002F20250522101009.png",[12,122,123,124,128,129,133],{},"Heads up — when you click in, the repo there is ",[125,126,127],"strong",{},"deprecated",". You'll need to click through to ",[59,130,131],{"href":131,"rel":132},"https:\u002F\u002Fgithub.com\u002Fgithub\u002Fgithub-mcp-server",[63]," to get to the latest version.",[12,135,136],{},[15,137],{"alt":119,"src":138},"https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002Fblog\u002Fai\u002Fmcp-github-copilot\u002F20250522101333.png",[12,140,141],{},"So what next? You might find yourself unable to spot any Docker or install commands, because the GitHub MCP Server installs through these two badges:",[12,143,144],{},[15,145],{"alt":146,"src":120},"Badges",[12,148,149],{},"These badges actually have install links wired up for you:",[151,152,157],"pre",{"className":153,"code":154,"language":155,"meta":156,"style":156},"language-bash shiki shiki-themes github-dark-high-contrast","https:\u002F\u002Finsiders.vscode.dev\u002Fredirect\u002Fmcp\u002Finstall?name=github&inputs=%5B%7B%22id%22%3A%22github_token%22%2C%22type%22%3A%22promptString%22%2C%22description%22%3A%22GitHub%20Personal%20Access%20Token%22%2C%22password%22%3Atrue%7D%5D&config=%7B%22command%22%3A%22docker%22%2C%22args%22%3A%5B%22run%22%2C%22-i%22%2C%22--rm%22%2C%22-e%22%2C%22GITHUB_PERSONAL_ACCESS_TOKEN%22%2C%22ghcr.io%2Fgithub%2Fgithub-mcp-server%22%5D%2C%22env%22%3A%7B%22GITHUB_PERSONAL_ACCESS_TOKEN%22%3A%22%24%7Binput%3Agithub_token%7D%22%7D%7D\n","bash","",[158,159,160],"code",{"__ignoreMap":156},[161,162,165,169,173,177,181,184,187,189],"span",{"class":163,"line":164},"line",1,[161,166,168],{"class":167},"s_sBn","https:\u002F\u002Finsiders.vscode.dev\u002Fredirect\u002Fmcp\u002Finstall?name",[161,170,172],{"class":171},"sTRMh","=github",[161,174,176],{"class":175},"sMAXC","&inputs",[161,178,180],{"class":179},"sWyjQ","=",[161,182,183],{"class":171},"%5B%7B%22id%22%3A%22github_token%22%2C%22type%22%3A%22promptString%22%2C%22description%22%3A%22GitHub%20Personal%20Access%20Token%22%2C%22password%22%3Atrue%7D%5D",[161,185,186],{"class":175},"&config",[161,188,180],{"class":179},[161,190,191],{"class":171},"%7B%22command%22%3A%22docker%22%2C%22args%22%3A%5B%22run%22%2C%22-i%22%2C%22--rm%22%2C%22-e%22%2C%22GITHUB_PERSONAL_ACCESS_TOKEN%22%2C%22ghcr.io%2Fgithub%2Fgithub-mcp-server%22%5D%2C%22env%22%3A%7B%22GITHUB_PERSONAL_ACCESS_TOKEN%22%3A%22%24%7Binput%3Agithub_token%7D%22%7D%7D\n",[12,193,194],{},"I'm demoing with the stable VSCode build here, since Insiders is a beta build — generally I'd advise regular users to avoid it.",[12,196,197],{},"When you click the link, a window pops up — pick \"Install Server\".",[12,199,200],{},[15,201],{"alt":202,"src":203},"Install Server","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002Fblog\u002Fai\u002Fmcp-github-copilot\u002F20250522102004.png",[12,205,206,207,210],{},"Then VSCode pops up the ",[158,208,209],{},"settings.json"," view with content like this:",[151,212,216],{"className":213,"code":214,"language":215,"meta":156,"style":156},"language-json shiki shiki-themes github-dark-high-contrast","{\n\"mcp\": {\n        \"servers\": {\n            \"github\": {\n                \"command\": \"docker\",\n                \"args\": [\n                    \"run\",\n                    \"-i\",\n                    \"--rm\",\n                    \"-e\",\n                    \"GITHUB_PERSONAL_ACCESS_TOKEN\",\n                    \"ghcr.io\u002Fgithub\u002Fgithub-mcp-server\"\n                ],\n                \"env\": {\n                    \"GITHUB_PERSONAL_ACCESS_TOKEN\": \"${input:github_token}\"\n                }\n            }\n        },\n        \"inputs\": [\n            {\n                \"id\": \"github_token\",\n                \"type\": \"promptString\",\n                \"description\": \"GitHub Personal Access Token\",\n                \"password\": true\n            }\n        ]\n    }\n}\n","json",[158,217,218,223,233,241,249,264,273,281,289,297,305,313,319,325,333,343,349,355,361,369,375,388,401,414,426,431,437,443],{"__ignoreMap":156},[161,219,220],{"class":163,"line":164},[161,221,222],{"class":175},"{\n",[161,224,226,230],{"class":163,"line":225},2,[161,227,229],{"class":228},"sKpQp","\"mcp\"",[161,231,232],{"class":175},": {\n",[161,234,236,239],{"class":163,"line":235},3,[161,237,238],{"class":228},"        \"servers\"",[161,240,232],{"class":175},[161,242,244,247],{"class":163,"line":243},4,[161,245,246],{"class":228},"            \"github\"",[161,248,232],{"class":175},[161,250,252,255,258,261],{"class":163,"line":251},5,[161,253,254],{"class":228},"                \"command\"",[161,256,257],{"class":175},": ",[161,259,260],{"class":171},"\"docker\"",[161,262,263],{"class":175},",\n",[161,265,267,270],{"class":163,"line":266},6,[161,268,269],{"class":228},"                \"args\"",[161,271,272],{"class":175},": [\n",[161,274,276,279],{"class":163,"line":275},7,[161,277,278],{"class":171},"                    \"run\"",[161,280,263],{"class":175},[161,282,284,287],{"class":163,"line":283},8,[161,285,286],{"class":171},"                    \"-i\"",[161,288,263],{"class":175},[161,290,292,295],{"class":163,"line":291},9,[161,293,294],{"class":171},"                    \"--rm\"",[161,296,263],{"class":175},[161,298,300,303],{"class":163,"line":299},10,[161,301,302],{"class":171},"                    \"-e\"",[161,304,263],{"class":175},[161,306,308,311],{"class":163,"line":307},11,[161,309,310],{"class":171},"                    \"GITHUB_PERSONAL_ACCESS_TOKEN\"",[161,312,263],{"class":175},[161,314,316],{"class":163,"line":315},12,[161,317,318],{"class":171},"                    \"ghcr.io\u002Fgithub\u002Fgithub-mcp-server\"\n",[161,320,322],{"class":163,"line":321},13,[161,323,324],{"class":175},"                ],\n",[161,326,328,331],{"class":163,"line":327},14,[161,329,330],{"class":228},"                \"env\"",[161,332,232],{"class":175},[161,334,336,338,340],{"class":163,"line":335},15,[161,337,310],{"class":228},[161,339,257],{"class":175},[161,341,342],{"class":171},"\"${input:github_token}\"\n",[161,344,346],{"class":163,"line":345},16,[161,347,348],{"class":175},"                }\n",[161,350,352],{"class":163,"line":351},17,[161,353,354],{"class":175},"            }\n",[161,356,358],{"class":163,"line":357},18,[161,359,360],{"class":175},"        },\n",[161,362,364,367],{"class":163,"line":363},19,[161,365,366],{"class":228},"        \"inputs\"",[161,368,272],{"class":175},[161,370,372],{"class":163,"line":371},20,[161,373,374],{"class":175},"            {\n",[161,376,378,381,383,386],{"class":163,"line":377},21,[161,379,380],{"class":228},"                \"id\"",[161,382,257],{"class":175},[161,384,385],{"class":171},"\"github_token\"",[161,387,263],{"class":175},[161,389,391,394,396,399],{"class":163,"line":390},22,[161,392,393],{"class":228},"                \"type\"",[161,395,257],{"class":175},[161,397,398],{"class":171},"\"promptString\"",[161,400,263],{"class":175},[161,402,404,407,409,412],{"class":163,"line":403},23,[161,405,406],{"class":228},"                \"description\"",[161,408,257],{"class":175},[161,410,411],{"class":171},"\"GitHub Personal Access Token\"",[161,413,263],{"class":175},[161,415,417,420,422],{"class":163,"line":416},24,[161,418,419],{"class":228},"                \"password\"",[161,421,257],{"class":175},[161,423,425],{"class":424},"sCcAr","true\n",[161,427,429],{"class":163,"line":428},25,[161,430,354],{"class":175},[161,432,434],{"class":163,"line":433},26,[161,435,436],{"class":175},"        ]\n",[161,438,440],{"class":163,"line":439},27,[161,441,442],{"class":175},"    }\n",[161,444,446],{"class":163,"line":445},28,[161,447,448],{"class":175},"}\n",[12,450,451,452,455],{},"At this point, the VSCode MCP Server config is done. Next we need to grab a GitHub Personal Access Token. The Token needs ",[158,453,454],{},"repo"," permissions for the MCP Server to work properly.",[20,457,459],{"id":458},"getting-a-github-personal-access-token","Getting a GitHub Personal Access Token",[12,461,462],{},"It's easy. Head to GitHub's settings page through this link:",[53,464,465],{},[56,466,467],{},[59,468,471],{"href":469,"rel":470},"https:\u002F\u002Fgithub.com\u002Fsettings\u002Fpersonal-access-tokens\u002Fnew",[63],"GitHub Personal Access Token",[12,473,474],{},"Here are the fields, for reference:",[53,476,477,480,483],{},[56,478,479],{},"Token name: GitHub MCP Server",[56,481,482],{},"Expiration: No expiration",[56,484,485],{},"Repository access: All repositories",[12,487,488],{},[15,489],{"alt":490,"src":491},"Get Token","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002Fblog\u002Fai\u002Fmcp-github-copilot\u002F20250522102440.png",[12,493,494],{},"Adjust the others to your needs — you can grant access to specific repositories only, for example.",[12,496,497],{},"Once you click \"Generate token\", you'll get a Token. Copy it somewhere — we'll use it shortly.",[12,499,500],{},[15,501],{"alt":490,"src":502},"https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002Fblog\u002Fai\u002Fmcp-github-copilot\u002F20250522102610.png",[504,505,506],"blockquote",{},[12,507,508,511],{},[125,509,510],{},"Note","\nDon't leak this Token to anyone.",[20,513,515],{"id":514},"setting-the-github-personal-access-token-in-vscode","Setting the GitHub Personal Access Token in VSCode",[12,517,518,519,522],{},"How do you input it? Hit ",[158,520,521],{},"F1"," to bring up the VSCode command palette and type:",[151,524,528],{"className":525,"code":526,"language":527,"meta":156,"style":156},"language-txt shiki shiki-themes github-dark-high-contrast",">MCP:List Servers\n","txt",[158,529,530],{"__ignoreMap":156},[161,531,532],{"class":163,"line":164},[161,533,526],{},[12,535,536],{},"You should see \"MCP: List Servers\". Pick that, then pick \"github\".",[12,538,539],{},[15,540],{"alt":541,"src":542},"Pick github","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002Fblog\u002Fai\u002Fmcp-github-copilot\u002F20250522103022.png",[12,544,545],{},"Then pick \"Start Server\". A window pops up asking for your GitHub Personal Access Token. Paste in the Token you just got and hit Enter.",[12,547,548],{},[15,549],{"alt":550,"src":551},"Enter Token","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002Fblog\u002Fai\u002Fmcp-github-copilot\u002F20250522103106.png",[12,553,554],{},"You'll see VSCode start the MCP Server and install Docker. Once you see this screen, the MCP Server has started successfully.",[12,556,557],{},[15,558],{"alt":559,"src":560},"Started successfully","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002Fblog\u002Fai\u002Fmcp-github-copilot\u002F20250522103141.png",[20,562,564],{"id":563},"testing-the-mcp-server","Testing the MCP Server",[12,566,567],{},"Time to test whether the MCP Server is actually working. Open GitHub Copilot Chat and switch to Agent mode.",[12,569,570],{},[15,571],{"alt":572,"src":573},"Agent Mode","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002Fblog\u002Fai\u002Fmcp-github-copilot\u002F20250522103719.png",[12,575,576],{},"Then start asking GitHub-related questions! Like... how many repositories are under my GitHub account?",[12,578,579],{},"If you see \"MCP server\" appear on screen, that means this request did go through the MCP Server before returning a result.",[12,581,582],{},[15,583],{"alt":584,"src":585},"Asking a question","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002Fblog\u002Fai\u002Fmcp-github-copilot\u002F20250522104000.png",[12,587,588],{},"So how do I know what features this MCP supports? Three ways:",[53,590,591,598],{},[56,592,593],{},[59,594,597],{"href":595,"rel":596},"https:\u002F\u002Fgithub.com\u002Fgithub\u002Fgithub-mcp-server?tab=readme-ov-file#tools",[63],"Official MCP Server Tools section",[56,599,600],{},"MCP Server Source Code",[12,602,603],{},"I'd recommend checking the \"Official MCP Server Tools section\" — that's the fastest path.",[12,605,606],{},"The other quick option is through GitHub Copilot Chat Tools.",[12,608,609],{},[15,610],{"alt":611,"src":612},"GitHub Copilot Chat Tools","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002Fblog\u002Fai\u002Fmcp-github-copilot\u002F20250522104418.png",[12,614,615],{},"Click into it and the GitHub Copilot Chat tools list pops up, listing all supported tools.",[12,617,618],{},[15,619],{"alt":611,"src":620},"https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002Fblog\u002Fai\u002Fmcp-github-copilot\u002F20250522104513.png",[12,622,623],{},"So that's the full GitHub Copilot + MCP Server VSCode walkthrough.",[12,625,626],{},"With MCP Server, you can ask the AI to do things more accurately — like creating a repository through natural language, and so on.",[628,629,630],"style",{},"html pre.shiki code .s_sBn, html code.shiki .s_sBn{--shiki-default:#FFB757}html pre.shiki code .sTRMh, html code.shiki .sTRMh{--shiki-default:#ADDCFF}html pre.shiki code .sMAXC, html code.shiki .sMAXC{--shiki-default:#F0F3F6}html pre.shiki code .sWyjQ, html code.shiki .sWyjQ{--shiki-default:#FF9492}html .default .shiki span {color: var(--shiki-default);background: var(--shiki-default-bg);font-style: var(--shiki-default-font-style);font-weight: var(--shiki-default-font-weight);text-decoration: var(--shiki-default-text-decoration);}html .shiki span {color: var(--shiki-default);background: var(--shiki-default-bg);font-style: var(--shiki-default-font-style);font-weight: var(--shiki-default-font-weight);text-decoration: var(--shiki-default-text-decoration);}html pre.shiki code .sKpQp, html code.shiki .sKpQp{--shiki-default:#72F088}html pre.shiki code .sCcAr, html code.shiki .sCcAr{--shiki-default:#91CBFF}",{"title":156,"searchDepth":225,"depth":225,"links":632},[633,634,635,636,637,638],{"id":22,"depth":225,"text":23},{"id":29,"depth":225,"text":30},{"id":91,"depth":225,"text":92},{"id":458,"depth":225,"text":459},{"id":514,"depth":225,"text":515},{"id":563,"depth":225,"text":564},"AI","2025-05-22 09:32:47","AI development has become a must-have skill for engineers, but when we use AI tools we often hit the same issues: the AI returns something we didn't expect, or it just doesn't get what we're asking for. These problems seriously hurt productivity. To solve this, MCP Server came along.","md","en",{},true,"\u002Fen\u002Fai\u002Fgithub-copilot-mcp-server-vscode-setup","4",{"title":6,"description":641},false,"en\u002FAI\u002Fgithub-copilot-mcp-server-vscode-setup",[639,71,652,653,654],"MCP Server","VSCode","Dev Workflow",null,"\u002Fen\u002Fai\u002F2025\u002F05\u002F22\u002Fgithub-copilot-mcp-server-vscode-setup\u002F","B8TeNmWEBKV_WbNTOzvHQVEWDUOB5OFpRCZ8jrPzmwA",{"newer":659,"older":663},{"url":660,"title":661,"date":662},"\u002Fen\u002Fai\u002F2025\u002F05\u002F23\u002Fbuild-your-own-mcp-server-github-copilot-chat\u002F","Build Your Own MCP Server for AI Agents — A Complete Implementation Guide With GitHub Copilot Chat","2025-05-23 15:02:03",{"url":664,"title":665,"date":666},"\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2025\u002F05\u002F21\u002Fgoogle-domains-shutdown-cloudflare-domain-tutorial\u002F","Google Domains Shut Down — Buying a Domain on Cloudflare and Deploying a Site, Step by Step","2025-05-21 10:16:44",[668,673,678],{"url":669,"title":670,"date":671,"readingMinutes":672},"\u002Fen\u002Fai\u002F2026\u002F06\u002F29\u002Fclaude-code-disable-mouse-clicks-env-var\u002F","New Claude Code Hijacks Mouse Clicks in Your Terminal? Kill It with CLAUDE_CODE_DISABLE_MOUSE_CLICKS","2026-06-29 18:00:00","3",{"url":674,"title":675,"date":676,"readingMinutes":677},"\u002Fen\u002Fai\u002F2026\u002F06\u002F27\u002Fdesign-md-google-design-system-for-ai-coding\u002F","design.md: If Your AI-Generated UI Keeps Drifting, You're Missing Google's design.md","2026-06-27 12:00:00","10",{"url":679,"title":680,"date":681,"readingMinutes":682},"\u002Fen\u002Fai\u002F2026\u002F06\u002F22\u002Fllms-txt-cloudflare-transform-rule-markdown-content-type\u002F","Make \u002Fllms.txt Return text\u002Fmarkdown on GitHub Pages: A Cloudflare Transform Rule Guide","2026-06-22 14:00:00","5",1784012764784]